Template: vitte/language
Type: select
Choices: English (en), Français (fr), Deutsch (de), Español (es), Italiano (it), 日本語 (ja), 한국어 (ko), 中文 (zh-CN), Nederlands (nl), Polski (pl), Português Brasileiro (pt-BR), Русский (ru), Türkçe (tr), Українська (uk), العربية (ar)
Choices-en: English (en), French (fr), German (de), Spanish (es), Italian (it), Japanese (ja), Korean (ko), Simplified Chinese (zh-CN), Dutch (nl), Polish (pl), Brazilian Portuguese (pt-BR), Russian (ru), Turkish (tr), Ukrainian (uk), Arabic (ar)
Default: English (en)
Description: Select your preferred language for Vitte
 Choose the language you want to use for Vitte messages and help text.
 You can change this later by running 'sudo vitte-configure-language'.

Template: vitte/language-note
Type: note
Description: Language configuration saved
 Your language preference has been saved to /etc/vitte/language.conf.
 To change it later, run: sudo /usr/bin/vitte-configure-language
